tring), args (string), etc. So yes, when calling mcp, set tool and args accordingly.\n\nSo first step: call mcp with tool aar_wait_for_opportunity and args \"{}\".\n\nSo the tool invocation would be:\n\n<tools>\n{\"name\": \"mcp\", \"arguments\": {\"tool\": \"aar_wait_for_opportunity\", \"args\": \"{}\"}}\n</tools>\n\nThat's the first step. Let's do that. Then process the response. Depending on the response, proceed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b9f90c55f2824ea0be4354","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_wait_for_opportunity","args":"{}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":2405,"output":609,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":3014,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782762190625,"responseId":"gen-1782762190-AHlISazOUS9roxn4UTCM","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}}
