nt starting at 00:00:50 with Infantino saying \"we are now going to do the draw.\"\n\nTherefore, the evidence does not support a preponderance standard that the \"Ronaldo\" statements were made \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" as defined by the market.\n\nSince the plaintiff has not proven by a preponderance of evidence that the statements were made during the market's specified time period, I should vote \"not_demonstrated\".\n\nLet's check the requirements for the response:\n- I need to call aar_submit_council_vote\n- Vote should be \"not_demonstrated\"\n- Rationale must be concise (no more than three sentences)\n\nRationale: The transcript evidence explicitly identifies Trump's Ronaldo mentions as occurring in remarks \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw,\" and the formal draw transcript contains no Ronaldo mention. The market terms do not include pre-event press exchanges as part of \"during\" the specific event of the Draw.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e784db7adc9340fcac5325","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\""},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762194999,"responseId":"gen-1782762195-IAAm4VEIvCT04Kf5K5V9","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to analyze the case thoroughly. This is an arbitration case about a Kalshi market where the question is whether Trump said \"Ronaldo\" during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\n\nLet me understand the core issue:\n- Market title: \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n- Strike: \"Ronaldo\"\n- The dispute is whether Trump saying \"Ronaldo\" in a pre-event reporter exchange immediately before the formal draw counts as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nLet me look at the evidence:\n\nPlaintiff's position:\n- PX-2: Transcript of remarks at Kennedy Center on December 5, 2025 titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n  - Contains multiple mentions of Ronaldo: \"I got to meet Ronaldo the other day, came to the White House. He was fantastic. He's a handsome guy and a great guy.\" and \"Believe it or not, I did. I did, and I loved it. I had a—I was okay. I wouldn't say—I was not Ronaldo or Messi. I was a little bit short of them.\"\n- PX-5: GovInfo metadata for that transcript\n- PX-3: The contract terms for PRESMENTION/NEWMENTION markets\n\nDefendant's position:\n- DX-6: Roll Call/Factba.se transcript of the formal FIFA World Cup Drawing program itself - shows nothing about Ronaldo\n- DX-4: The same contract terms as PX-3\n- They emphasize that the transcript evidence plaintiff relies on is explicitly titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nContract terms analysis:\n- The underlying is \"words used by entity during time period\"\n- TIME PERIOD definition: \"when a time period refers to a specific event, the Exchange may specify what is included\"\n- Technical details: \"When time period refers to a specific event, pre-recorded content broadcast, streamed, or published as part of that event is included IF presented as part of the official presentation.\"\n- \"Behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nKey evidentiary points:\n\n1. Plaintiff's evidence (PX-2/PX-5):\n   - A public presidential transcript of remarks at the John F. Kennedy Center at 11:13 a.m. December 5, 2025\n   - Title explicitly: \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n   - FIFA President Infantino present\n   - Discussion about the World Cup Draw, ticket sales, etc.\n   - Contains multiple mentions of \"Ronaldo\"\n   - Official GovInfo publication (part of Federal Register), NARA, etc.\n\n2. Defendant's evidence (DX-6):\n   - The actual formal FIFA World Cup Drawing transcript\n   - Clearly separated from the pre-event reporter exchange\n   - Contains no mention of Ronaldo\n   - Includes Infantino saying \"this is the World Cup trophy... we are now going to do the draw\" at 00:00:50 (which seems to mark the start of the formal draw)\n\n3. Contract terms:\n   - \"When time period refers to a specific event, the Exchange may specify what is included\"\n   - \"Behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nImportant analysis points:\n\n- The market title is \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" - it does NOT explicitly say \"during the formal draw program only\" or \"excluding pre-event press remarks\"\n- However, the transcript evidence itself is explicitly titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n- The formal Draw transcript appears to be a distinct document with its own timing (starting at 00:00:50 with Infantino saying \"we are now going to do the draw\")\n- The plaintiff's own evidence treats the reporter exchange as \"prior to\" the Draw, not \"during\" it\n\n- The contract terms require the word to be said during the time period, and the time period is specified as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n- The terms state: \"When time period refers to a specific event... behind-the-scenes content... are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n- This reporter exchange appears to be pre-event remarks that happened at the venue but before the formal draw began\n\nThe issue is whether \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" in the market title could reasonably include this pre-event press exchange where Trump mentioned \"Ronaldo\" multiple times.\n\nLet's examine the context:\n\n1. The plaintiff argues that \"during\" should include the event-linked remarks immediately before the formal program\n2. The defendant argues that \"during\" refers to the formal Draw itself, which had a separate transcript\n\nThe transcript evidence itself says \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\" - this title is significant.\n\nAccording to the contract terms: \"When time period refers to a specific event (such as an address, speech, performance, or broadcast), the Exchange may specify what is included, including whether it includes both live and pre-recorded segments (including whether advertisements are included).\"\n\nBut crucially, the market page did not specify what was included - it just said \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The plaintiff argues the market should be interpreted broadly, while defendant argues for a strict interpretation based on the title of the transcript evidence.\n\nThe terms also state: \"When time period refers to a specific event... the Exchange may specify what is included... behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nIs this reporter exchange considered:\n- Official broadcast as part of the Draw? (the market page doesn't specify)\n- Part of the event? (the transcript says \"Prior to\")\n- Or separate from the formal Draw itself? (the separate formal transcript exists)\n\nThe evidence appears to support that this was a separate pre-event press availability, not actually part of the formal drawing program.\n\nI see that:\n- The formal Draw transcript includes Infantino saying \"this is the World Cup trophy... we are now going to do the draw\" at 00:00:50\n- Trump's press exchange was before this point (at 11:13 AM as documented in the GovInfo metadata)\n- The transcript is titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nIn contract terms, when a market says \"during a specific event,\" it typically means during the event itself, not including things that happened before it.\n\nFor example, if a market said \"during the State of the Union address,\" it would not include events happening the day before, even at the same venue.\n\nHere, the evidence explicitly marks the reporter exchange as \"prior to\" the draw, and there's a separate formal draw transcript that begins with Infantino stating \"we are now going to do the draw,\" which appears to mark the start of the formal event.\n\nBased on the admitted evidence:\n\n- The market title alone is not specific about what \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" includes\n- However, the record itself is clear that the statements in question were \"prior to\" the draw\n- There's no evidence showing that the official market terms or the market page included pre-event press exchanges in the \"during\" period\n\nThe plaintiff argues that the absence of an explicit exclusion means the broader interpretation should apply. But the burden of proof is on the plaintiff to show that it's more likely than not that the pre-event press exchange falls within the market's time period.\n\nThe admitted evidence does not support that conclusion. The plaintiff's own evidence calls it \"prior to\" the draw, not \"during\" the draw. The formal draw transcript appears to be a distinct event starting at 00:00:50 with Infantino saying \"we are now going to do the draw.\"\n\nTherefore, the evidence does not support a preponderance standard that the \"Ronaldo\" statements were made \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" as defined by the market.\n\nSince the plaintiff has not proven by a preponderance of evidence that the statements were made during the market's specified time period, I should vote \"not_demonstrated\".\n\nLet's check the requirements for the response:\n- I need to call aar_submit_council_vote\n- Vote should be \"not_demonstrated\"\n- Rationale must be concise (no more than three sentences)\n\nRationale: The transcript evidence explicitly identifies Trump's Ronaldo mentions as occurring in remarks \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw,\" and the formal draw transcript contains no Ronaldo mention. The market terms do not include pre-event press exchanges as part of \"during\" the specific event of the Draw.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e784db7adc9340fcac5325","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\""},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762194999,"responseId":"gen-1782762195-IAAm4VEIvCT04Kf5K5V9","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":"Transcript evidence explicitly identifies","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to analyze the case thoroughly. This is an arbitration case about a Kalshi market where the question is whether Trump said \"Ronaldo\" during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\n\nLet me understand the core issue:\n- Market title: \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n- Strike: \"Ronaldo\"\n- The dispute is whether Trump saying \"Ronaldo\" in a pre-event reporter exchange immediately before the formal draw counts as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nLet me look at the evidence:\n\nPlaintiff's position:\n- PX-2: Transcript of remarks at Kennedy Center on December 5, 2025 titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n  - Contains multiple mentions of Ronaldo: \"I got to meet Ronaldo the other day, came to the White House. He was fantastic. He's a handsome guy and a great guy.\" and \"Believe it or not, I did. I did, and I loved it. I had a—I was okay. I wouldn't say—I was not Ronaldo or Messi. I was a little bit short of them.\"\n- PX-5: GovInfo metadata for that transcript\n- PX-3: The contract terms for PRESMENTION/NEWMENTION markets\n\nDefendant's position:\n- DX-6: Roll Call/Factba.se transcript of the formal FIFA World Cup Drawing program itself - shows nothing about Ronaldo\n- DX-4: The same contract terms as PX-3\n- They emphasize that the transcript evidence plaintiff relies on is explicitly titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nContract terms analysis:\n- The underlying is \"words used by entity during time period\"\n- TIME PERIOD definition: \"when a time period refers to a specific event, the Exchange may specify what is included\"\n- Technical details: \"When time period refers to a specific event, pre-recorded content broadcast, streamed, or published as part of that event is included IF presented as part of the official presentation.\"\n- \"Behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nKey evidentiary points:\n\n1. Plaintiff's evidence (PX-2/PX-5):\n   - A public presidential transcript of remarks at the John F. Kennedy Center at 11:13 a.m. December 5, 2025\n   - Title explicitly: \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n   - FIFA President Infantino present\n   - Discussion about the World Cup Draw, ticket sales, etc.\n   - Contains multiple mentions of \"Ronaldo\"\n   - Official GovInfo publication (part of Federal Register), NARA, etc.\n\n2. Defendant's evidence (DX-6):\n   - The actual formal FIFA World Cup Drawing transcript\n   - Clearly separated from the pre-event reporter exchange\n   - Contains no mention of Ronaldo\n   - Includes Infantino saying \"this is the World Cup trophy... we are now going to do the draw\" at 00:00:50 (which seems to mark the start of the formal draw)\n\n3. Contract terms:\n   - \"When time period refers to a specific event, the Exchange may specify what is included\"\n   - \"Behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nImportant analysis points:\n\n- The market title is \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" - it does NOT explicitly say \"during the formal draw program only\" or \"excluding pre-event press remarks\"\n- However, the transcript evidence itself is explicitly titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n- The formal Draw transcript appears to be a distinct document with its own timing (starting at 00:00:50 with Infantino saying \"we are now going to do the draw\")\n- The plaintiff's own evidence treats the reporter exchange as \"prior to\" the Draw, not \"during\" it\n\n- The contract terms require the word to be said during the time period, and the time period is specified as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n- The terms state: \"When time period refers to a specific event... behind-the-scenes content... are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n- This reporter exchange appears to be pre-event remarks that happened at the venue but before the formal draw began\n\nThe issue is whether \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" in the market title could reasonably include this pre-event press exchange where Trump mentioned \"Ronaldo\" multiple times.\n\nLet's examine the context:\n\n1. The plaintiff argues that \"during\" should include the event-linked remarks immediately before the formal program\n2. The defendant argues that \"during\" refers to the formal Draw itself, which had a separate transcript\n\nThe transcript evidence itself says \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\" - this title is significant.\n\nAccording to the contract terms: \"When time period refers to a specific event (such as an address, speech, performance, or broadcast), the Exchange may specify what is included, including whether it includes both live and pre-recorded segments (including whether advertisements are included).\"\n\nBut crucially, the market page did not specify what was included - it just said \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The plaintiff argues the market should be interpreted broadly, while defendant argues for a strict interpretation based on the title of the transcript evidence.\n\nThe terms also state: \"When time period refers to a specific event... the Exchange may specify what is included... behind-the-scenes content, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings are NOT included unless officially broadcast or published as part of time period.\"\n\nIs this reporter exchange considered:\n- Official broadcast as part of the Draw? (the market page doesn't specify)\n- Part of the event? (the transcript says \"Prior to\")\n- Or separate from the formal Draw itself? (the separate formal transcript exists)\n\nThe evidence appears to support that this was a separate pre-event press availability, not actually part of the formal drawing program.\n\nI see that:\n- The formal Draw transcript includes Infantino saying \"this is the World Cup trophy... we are now going to do the draw\" at 00:00:50\n- Trump's press exchange was before this point (at 11:13 AM as documented in the GovInfo metadata)\n- The transcript is titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n\nIn contract terms, when a market says \"during a specific event,\" it typically means during the event itself, not including things that happened before it.\n\nFor example, if a market said \"during the State of the Union address,\" it would not include events happening the day before, even at the same venue.\n\nHere, the evidence explicitly marks the reporter exchange as \"prior to\" the draw, and there's a separate formal draw transcript that begins with Infantino stating \"we are now going to do the draw,\" which appears to mark the start of the formal event.\n\nBased on the admitted evidence:\n\n- The market title alone is not specific about what \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" includes\n- However, the record itself is clear that the statements in question were \"prior to\" the draw\n- There's no evidence showing that the official market terms or the market page included pre-event press exchanges in the \"during\" period\n\nThe plaintiff argues that the absence of an explicit exclusion means the broader interpretation should apply. But the burden of proof is on the plaintiff to show that it's more likely than not that the pre-event press exchange falls within the market's time period.\n\nThe admitted evidence does not support that conclusion. The plaintiff's own evidence calls it \"prior to\" the draw, not \"during\" the draw. The formal draw transcript appears to be a distinct event starting at 00:00:50 with Infantino saying \"we are now going to do the draw.\"\n\nTherefore, the evidence does not support a preponderance standard that the \"Ronaldo\" statements were made \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" as defined by the market.\n\nSince the plaintiff has not proven by a preponderance of evidence that the statements were made during the market's specified time period, I should vote \"not_demonstrated\".\n\nLet's check the requirements for the response:\n- I need to call aar_submit_council_vote\n- Vote should be \"not_demonstrated\"\n- Rationale must be concise (no more than three sentences)\n\nRationale: The transcript evidence explicitly identifies Trump's Ronaldo mentions as occurring in remarks \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw,\" and the formal draw transcript contains no Ronaldo mention. The market terms do not include pre-event press exchanges as part of \"during\" the specific event of the Draw.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e784db7adc9340fcac5325","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Transcript evidence explicitly identifies"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Transcript evidence explicitly identifies","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762194999,"responseId":"gen-1782762195-IAAm4VEIvCT04Kf5K5V9","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to analyze the case thoroughly. This is an arbitration case about a Kalshi market where the question is whether Trump said \"Ronal